did.abstract: Clippings, biographical information forms, correspondence, articles, and other items gathered by the Alumnae and Alumni of Vassar College (AAVC) on women who attended the college from 1865-1942 and 1951-1958. The collection includes material on graduates, non-graduates, Special Students and Preparatory Students.

bioghist.head: Administrative History
bioghist.p: The Associated Alumnae of Vassar College (AAVC) was formed in 1871. The name was changed in 1970 to Alumnae and Alumni of Vassar College to reflect the institution's acceptance of male students. It has always been an independent organization, rather than a department of Vassar College. The purposes of the AAVC include raising money for scholarships, providing a network of support for students after graduation, and enabling the exchange of information between the college and its graduates.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: Clippings, biographical information forms, correspondence, articles, and other items gathered by the Alumnae and Alumni of Vassar College (AAVC) on women who attended the college from 1865-1942 and 1951-1958. The collection includes material on graduates, non-graduates, Special Students and Preparatory Students. Note: The container list for this collection does not constitute a complete alumnae/i listing; not every graduate is represented.

accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: Files from members of the Class of 1931 and later are currently closed to research. The rest of this collection is open for research according to the regulations of the Vassar College Archives and Special Collections Library without any additional restrictions.

userestrict.head: Restrictions on Use
userestrict.p: Permission to quote (publish) from unpublished or previously published material must be obtained as described in the regulations of the Vassar College Archives and Special Collections Library.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is arranged by class year, then alphabetically by last name. Note: some students were assigned a class year, or chose to identify with a specific class, regardless of when or if they actually graduated.
